INSERT INTO `tbl_activities_about` VALUES (2,5,'<p>hgjghj gjgh jghj</p>\n'),(3,7,'<p><strong>Paragliding</strong><span style=\"color:rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family:arial,sans-serif; font-size:16px\">&nbsp;is the recreational and competitive adventure sport of flying&nbsp;</span><strong>paragliders</strong><span style=\"color:rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family:arial,sans-serif; font-size:16px\">: lightweight, free-flying, foot-launched glider aircraft with no rigid primary structure. The pilot sits in a harness suspended below a fabric wing.</span></p>\n'),(4,17,'<p>This being India&rsquo;s highest and most daring jumps, is a dream adventure of all those who love to experience the thrilling rush of adrenaline. Bungee jumping is an extreme adventure sport which let you fall free from an erected platform much above from the ground where you will be attached to an elastic chord.</p>\n'),(5,9,'<p>Rishikesh is the place where we experience another face of river Ganges. With a large concentration of class 3 and class 4 rapids, this is n absolute rafting destination. Having these rapids along 40 km stretch, this place offers a mind blowing rafting experience.</p>\n'),(6,6,'<p>Kayaking<span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">&nbsp;is the use of a kayak&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">for moving across water.A kayak is a low-to-the-water, canoe-like boat in which the paddler sits facing forward, legs in front, using a double-bladed paddle to pull front-to-back on one side and then the other in rotation.</span></p>\n'),(7,19,'<p>Scuba stands for Self Contained Underwater Breathing Apparatus. While scuba diving has been popular among a large number of people abroad, the idea is rather new for many Indian.</p>\n\n<p>Scuba diving is safe..the gear, that weighs almost 14kgs ensures that no matter what happens, you will be safe. Once you are in the water, the 14kgs is reduced to mere &quot;Weightlessness&quot; due to the law of physics.</p>\n'),(1,5,'<p>Meesapulimala Peak trek is a trek through lush green valleys, hundreds of blooming Rhododendrons, charming tea estates, gurgling brooks &ndash; peace is easy to find in the idyllic surroundings of Meesapulimala. Located at a significant altitude of 8,661 feet in the Idukki district of Kerala, Meesapulimala is a trek through eight hills, passing through the shared border of Tamil Nadu and Kerala.</p>\n\n<p>This 8 km trek from Rhodovalley takes you through high altitude grasslands, rainforests and wildlife. The&nbsp;Meesapulima Peak is called so because it apparently resembles a tiger&rsquo;s face, although you&rsquo;re not likely to spot any tiger here. &ldquo;Meesa,&rdquo; means moustache, &ldquo;puli,&rdquo; means tiger and &ldquo;mala,&rdquo; means hill. Hence, it is from this that the peak gets its name from and this is why it is called so.</p>\n\n<p>This is just a day&rsquo;s trek and hence trekkers of any age can go for this trek. There are plenty&nbsp;scenic spot in this trek that trekkers can enjoy and capture. It is a easy to moderate trek and therefore can be completed without any hindrances.(Author: Usha Hariprasad)</p>\n');
