INSERT INTO `tbl_exp_stays_about` VALUES (4,4,'<p>test</p>\n'),(3,5,'<p>test</p>\n'),(14,5,'<p>Ambady Estate offers luxurious rooms and a beautiful and well-maintained garden amid a picturesque setting, located in Munnar, one of India&rsquo;s most exotic destinations. situated in the tranquil Western Ghats, Ambady Estate is wrapped in the cool embrace of the Sahya rainforest, surrounded by awe-inspiring Parvathy Hills on one side, and the marvelous view of the &lsquo;Chokkan Mala&rsquo;, Idukki Dam, and the tea plantations on the other sides. Spread across seventy acres, our plantation is home to diverse and indigenous flora and fauna. Ambady is the place to recreate the synergy of mind, body and intellect through our serene ambience, nutritious and healthy food, the bird song and starlight and the melody of nature.</p>\n'),(6,3,'<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif; font-size:14.4px\">Chokramudi stands as a unique piece of Elevated Mountain at an altitude of almost 7200 feet.Unlike the other hill ranges in Idukki it pose&nbsp;separately and is not attached to any other hills or ranges of hills in Munnar.The base camp of Chokramudi peak is a wonderful experience for those who love to explore the heights.The mysterious calmness and breathtaking views from the camp itself is a unique&nbsp;experience.Grabbing a portion of BBQ and gather around a bonfire with music adds to the unconditional experience of being on the standalone peak under the glazing stars.The off road drive to the campsite and speculative&nbsp;trek to the top of Chokramudi render&nbsp;the lust&nbsp;of adventure junkies who loves to experience the rare.</span></p>\n'),(25,10,'<p>testing</p>\n'),(7,2,'<p>The tree houses are spacious and suitably laid out. It has a balcony that offers some magnificent views of the jungle and the valley. It is presented in a perfect way so as to enjoy the best that nature offers. The tree trunk passing through the room added to its appeal. Even though these&nbsp;<strong>tree houses</strong>&nbsp;is&nbsp;committed to nature, Comforts are not compromised. Luxury is built into the interiors of these tree houses. The tree houses are located amidst wilderness. It&rsquo;s not easy walking up to&nbsp;<strong>tree house</strong>. Can hear the Chirping and screeching of birds mingled with the rhythmic beat of waters cascading down the stream. Sight of monkeys dance around from one tree to the other, some deers and even python are also some views from tree house.</p>\n'),(8,3,'<p>You will notice all these dwelling places only if someone points them out to you! Luxury at its best form is being built into the interiors of these tents, without compromising on our eco-drive. Superior quality coir flooring, Bamboo &amp; Paper light fittings, eco-friendly toiletries, etc are just some of the eco-friendly initiatives you will experience in your room.</p>\n\n<p>While we are totally committed to the nature, we have not compromised on any of your comforts. Each cottage has Well-appointed rooms with modern bath rooms and large varandahs, and surrounded by aromatic plants like Lavender and Rosemary.</p>\n\n<p>Comfortable Valley view African Safari Tents</p>\n\n<p>The tent is comfortable and well fixed. Even though These&nbsp;<strong>Safari Tents</strong>&nbsp;is&nbsp;committed to nature, Comforts are not compromised. Luxury is built into the interiors of these tents. It is perfectly clean with supply of hot water. Beds are covered with mosquito nets and tidy linens to keep warm. Staying in the tent to be very warm and comfortable. It will be a beautiful experience sleeping in the middle of a jungle. The view can be amazing and have only nature all around you. The staff will be friendly. Food can be awesome.</p>\n'),(27,3,'<p>Camping over the clouds...!! Does it seems a fantacy ..? Absolutly not. One can experience the joy of being watching the world from sky.Yes it is possible by staying on the top of a mighty peak in Munnar and enjoy the clouds that pass beneath under your foots..</p>\n'),(28,2,'<p>This Plantation tree house is surrounded by tea, coffee, pepper and cardamom plantations.&nbsp;One can experience the presence of more than hundreds oflarge trees.&nbsp; It is a paradise for birds and you would love to watch squirrels running up and down.&nbsp;In the night, listen to the chants of beetles and if you&rsquo;re lucky, you could see hundreds of fireflies lighting up the trees.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;It is a fantastic place for adventurous families, a hide out for romantic couples, haven for nature lovers or a camping place for a group of friends.As a family we would love to welcome&nbsp; and assist our guests to have a wonderful holiday.</p>\n'),(29,5,'<p>This stone structure exudes a rustic charm in sync with nature and offers some of the best spectacles around. Built without causing any damage to the natural attributes and landscape of the location, this resort has three units.&nbsp; The main block that houses the common areas like reception, lounge, dining and kitchen and another two stone building that has twelve tastefully done up cottages. The large windows and louvers of the cottages let in plenty of natural light and air while the rich teak wood furniture and the hand made lamps ensure a touch of ethnic feel. The guests are ensured of some of the most modern amenities and facilities in this resort to ensure a reclusive holiday without being cut off from the outside world. Four tree-top house in midst of plantation provides an experience of being connected with nature at close proximity. Waking up with listening to birds, beetles, crickets and sun-rays provides ideal setup for rejuvenating holidays. A desk in between the tree house provides open space for contemplating with nature. The Farm yard is the main attraction of the retreat theme of organic living and dining. You would love to take a stroll along its full fledged vegetable and fruit garden or the rose garden. The well tended spice plantation allows you to take a closer look at the farming activities and if interested, you can try out a hand too! What you can like the best will be the campfire in this resort that will tempt you to stay awake late into night, under the starlit sky.&nbsp;</p>\n'),(30,5,'<p>It is surrounded by charismatic eucalyptus trees and a meandering brook downhill giving a soul-soothening welcome note. The locale gifts you a rejuvenating effect and pleasent accomodation in munnar with the clean and soft smell of the medicinal eucalyptus unfurling from the surroundings.</p>\n\n<p>It&nbsp;<span style=\"color:#333534; font-family:opensansregular,serif\">offers a special Twin Cottage which can accommodate two families, with two plush bedrooms, 2 bathrooms with bath tub facility and a common sit-out. This Cottage in Munnar is ideal for sharing memorable vacationing moments between friends with the same travel destination in mind.</span></p>\n'),(31,10,'<p>The Rain is a venture by the Johns Group of Companies, who has been popular in and outside Kerala for their magnificent repute of bringing Kerala together under the comfort of their umbrellas during the drizzly days of monsoon. Johns with their roots in Kerala has been in the umbrella making business for the past seventy years being one of the earliest Indian pioneers in umbrella manufacturing industry. Johns has a reputation for going all-out to ensure that every product they offer in the market is committed to quality, safety, and good value for money. The company&rsquo;s attention to detail and an innate urge to keep their customers happy always is what initiated them to launch The Rain, a perfect setting where people can smile and instantly relax their senses.</p>\n'),(32,10,'<p>It is a Premium waterfront Serviced Villa situated in Aluva, nearly 10 km away from Cochin International Airport. One can experience a complete nature friendly stay in the middle of the city.</p>\n'),(33,8,'<p>It is&nbsp;an enchanting haven nestled in the evergreen verdure of the hilly tropical rainforest, with its splendid waterfalls, inviting plunge pools and its soothing sedate serenity lures the southern sojourner. Green Trees the boutique resort, perched within the lush green forests of Athirappilly is a surreal abode that seamlessly etches on to the fabric of the forest.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n'),(34,10,'<p>It is exquisitely landscaped with lagoons and canals meandering in and around a number of cottages (heritage &amp; modern) built around picturesque greenery overlooking the clean beach at the front and serene backwaters behind. Amongst these are traditional heritage Fishermen villas facing backwaters &amp; the Modern villas fully air-conditioned and with all modern facilities. The resort is designed with love and style. Each and every detail is just perfect.</p>\n\n<p>Sun rises at the backwater side of the resorts &ndash; first you see a wave of crimson at the eastern horizon. As and when it approaches Cherai, it thickens to molten gold and in minutes you see it merging with the ubiquitous skies and backwaters turning everything in and around it into a maze of crimson yellowish gold. The sun sets in front of the resorts in the Arabian Sea.</p>\n'),(35,11,'<p>It is a luxury Air-conditioned houseboat with 3 Luxuries a/c bedrooms, a living Area, 01 of the room with an exclusive Private balcony, Airconditioned dining area, Roof top/ Moon Dining &amp; a Sunset deck. This boat can accommodate upto 09 Adults at a time for overnight stay &amp; Can cater upto 75 persons for a day cruise or Parties.</p>\n\n<p>It also includes a sun terrace. Guests can enjoy a meal at the on-site restaurant. The property also offers packed lunches.</p>\n'),(36,11,'<p>The house boat is completely furnished and has rooms with sundeck, comfortable chairs, kitchen and toilet with A/C. Full-Fledged Conference Facility is a distinguishing and an outstanding feature of our Houseboat. The modern Houseboats you see are a reworked model of the &quot;Kettuvallams&quot; which were used to carry rice and spices from Kuttanad to Kochi Port. This marvel in naval architecture is about 60 to 70 feet long and about 15 feet wide at the middle. The glittering water and the soothing calm and cool breeze is an enticement that an Houseboat can offer - an exclusive and exceptional experience that touches you with the vigour and vitality of the countryside of the God&#39;s Own Country. An added wonderful experience while in Alappuzha is a houseboat cruise. Our houseboat cover all amenities and comforts of a good hotel such as secure and furnished bedrooms, modern toilets, comfy living rooms, a kitchen and even a balcony for angling.</p>\n'),(37,11,'<p><span style=\"font-family:open sans,sans-serif; font-size:14px\">These houseboats have been adapted to accommodate all modern conveniences, sun decks, living rooms, dining rooms, bedrooms, uninterrupted water supply and a well-stocked kitchen and skilled crew who ensure you have a luxurious experience. Every houseboat has a three member crew consisting of a driver, assistant and a cook.</span></p>\n'),(38,9,'<p>It is situated in 370 Acers of Plantations and Farm.&nbsp; This is one of the most and inspirational Resort in Munnar, Kerala. A Home From a destination, Kerala has evolved into an addiction for tourists across the globe because of the sheer beauty of the land and a people known for their open hearts and generous hospitality. At Dew Drops resorts we take hospitality to a higher altitude. The doors of our home are opened wide as we bid you warm welcome.</p>\n'),(39,5,'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family:signika,sans-serif\">Rock House rooms are a two bedroom elevated cottage with two seperate rooms and a common balcony. The rooms have seperate doors and bathrooms. The room is relatively smaller in size, similar to that of the tree house and has a double cot, which mean two adults can only be accommodated. The rock house rooms would be ideal for families or couples&nbsp;who would require two adjacent rooms under one roof.</span></span></p>\n'),(40,3,'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:rgb(65, 65, 65); font-family:signika,sans-serif\">The luxury tents are quite large and are on top of a hillock, you will have to climb up around 35 steps and slopes to reach the tents. The higher you climb, the more beautiful the view. Since they are quite large, there is ample space for two additional mattresses in the Luxury tents, which means 4 guests can easily be accommodated with two additional extra mattresses. The tent has an exclusive sit out and has an amazing view. Ideal for small groups of friends or team outing who would love to stay under one roof.</span></span></p>\n'),(41,8,'<p>The first and only complete suite room resort in Munnar&rdquo;&nbsp;situates in Letchmi tea estate surrounded by rain forest, cardamom and firewood plantation. The flora and fauna, lush canopy of tropical trees, plantation waterfall distinguish this plantation resort&nbsp;as different from other resorts in Munnar.</p>\n\n<p>Every suite has a large bath room, 350 sq ft living area with private office space and dining area, private balcony overlooking to the rain forest. The large bed room and its ethnic architecture welcomes every guest to a unique experience.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Automated heated swimming pool nestled right front of 90 cover restaurant and open terrace gazebo dining, 3000 sq ft rose garden and the enchanting natural beauty of the rain forest make memorable experience for honeymooners.&nbsp;</p>\n'),(42,8,'<p>It is&nbsp;an exclusive plantation cottages tucked away from the usual tourist route inside a scenic forest on the Munnar. With a natural waterfall on its premises and a gurgling stream flowing alongside the rooms, this nature resort presents a perfect wilderness getaway.</p>\n'),(43,2,'<p>The Tree House is a fantastic accommodation for 3 adults. It comes with a queen bed, a TV, wardrobe and 24-hour room and laundry service. We also provide complimentary breakfast. It also has separate living area and a balcony with a breathtaking view.</p>\n'),(44,8,'<p>This Plantation cottage&nbsp;has&nbsp;a slice of privacy and comfortable-living in the most serene location you can ask for!<br />\n<br />\nWe provide you a separate living area and balcony. The room has a queen size bed, a television and wardrobe. 24-hour room and laundry services are also provided to you.</p>\n'),(45,5,'<p>All rooms at this premium villa is open out to a breathtaking view of the hills.<br />\nIt has one of the largest and best designed furnished suites at Munnar. You may also enjoy the comforts of hill views serene of&nbsp;other rooms, which are equally stylish and comfortable</p>\n'),(9,9,'<p>&nbsp;An Eco &amp; Nature Resort Spread across 35 acres of verdant terrain and tucked away at an altitude of 3500 feet above sea level, andstands in the middle of a tropical forest with exotic flora and fauna.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Constructed using mud excavated from the very site that it stands onthe very site that it stands on the resort is a fine example of rammed earth architecture, and a glowing tribute to vernacular construction methods. its unique rustic look&nbsp;offering the best in luxury and comfort is truly&nbsp;&quot;Heaven made of Earth.&quot;Thousands of Guadua bamboo saplings planted around the resort create a bio-fencing while improving the already pristine air quality.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;Its dark wooden interiors create an ambience that is&nbsp;intimate and romantic, andbewitching beauty of the natural surrounding&nbsp;is bound to leave you awestruck, is a favorite honeymooners&#39; haunt.</p>\n'),(10,8,'<p><span style=\"color:rgb(69, 50, 28); font-family:pt sans,sans-serif; font-size:14.6667px\">Set along the slope of a forest clad hill, beside three branches of a sprightly mountain stream that forks as it flows through the 150 acre property, coming together and broadening at the end of the slope, this luxury plantation cottage&nbsp;is an exquisite jungle hideaway and a naturalist&#39;s treasure trove. Wrapped in the enchantment of a tropical rainforest, beneath an enormous interlaced canopy formed by majestic trees, stone paved paths fringed by tropical plants wind through leading to brick coloured cottages, designed in architecture influenced to a great extent by the vernacular of the region. Built with wooden rafters on the roof and parquet flooring, furnished in wood and fabrics in a palette of earth colours - the accommodations are spacious, equipped with the state of the art in amenities and verandas that look out at fabulous views of the forest - an intimate experience of the surrounding sights and sounds</span></p>\n'),(11,8,'<p>Experiential Plantation Resort</p>\n'),(46,6,'<p>It&nbsp;is a 55yr old heritage bungalow set amidst an evergreen sprawling 20acres of lush green dense spice plantation.It is just 2.5kms from the famous and the Kerala&#39;s 2nd biggest waterfall - MEENMUTTY WATERFALLS. It&nbsp;have very artistically &amp; tastefully done 04 Well-furnished and spacious en-suite rooms having an Each room panoramic 360-degree view of coffee estate. Each rooms are having 02 King sized beds and all rooms are having LCD TV and modern bathrooms with the toiletries to meet the guests end.</p>\n'),(47,6,'<p>It is a restored heritage property featuring independent twin bungalows built in the 50&rsquo;s for the sterling companies in Cochin. They represent an archetypal British colonial style settlement in Fort Kochi from the middle of the last century. Each bungalow houses three bedrooms, a dining room overlooking its own private pool and a fully equipped kitchen with an on-call chef.</p>\n'),(48,6,'<p>This is inspired from its colonial history. A former shipyard in British times, it has been converted by us to faithfully reflect the symbols and signs of a historical period known for its stately grandeur and good taste as expressed through its ambiance, amenities, service and food.</p>\n'),(49,6,'<p>Built by blending contemporary and colonial styles each room has a distinct appeal. The echoes from the past come alive here while the air carries an unmistakable sweet scent.</p>\n'),(50,5,'<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>&nbsp;A serene aryurvedic resort located by the riverside, the resort combines the pleasure of a forest atmosphere with authentic ayurveda treatment and wellness therapies. The resort has all the facilities to make your stay relaxed, comfortable and rejuvenating. Overlooking the shimmering waters of periyar and nestled among lush green Mahagony forests, the resort&nbsp;offers you a chance to unwind and have a holiday of a life-time, while simultaneously rejuvenating your body and mind through effective, efficient Ayurvedic treatments. Spread out to offer nature&rsquo;s view for your getaway accommodation . Ideal for a relaxing holiday to renew your spirits.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n'),(51,3,'<p><span style=\"color:rgb(127, 127, 127); font-family:poppins,sans-serif; font-size:14.5px\">This Camping is ideal for everyone, featuring flexible adventures and activities that allow you to challenge your inner athlete, or relax and enjoy the scenery. We got excited while planning this adventure tour and crammed in as many incredible experiences as you could possibly handle. Perfect guided tour for anyone, from ultra-athlete to first timers and avid relaxers, with highly adaptable adventures and activities. Start early to enjoy the incredible view of this scenic location.</span></p>\n'),(52,2,'<p><span style=\"color:black; font-family:arial,sans-serif; font-size:9.5pt\">The tree house&nbsp;set in a 200-acre colonial coffee and spice plantation in the&nbsp;verdant&nbsp;hills of Wayanad, North Kerala&nbsp;offer modern luxury, right up amongst the treetops.&nbsp;Featuring large bedrooms, outdoor living spaces and safari-inspired furniture, our tree houses offer a truly elevating experience.</span></p>\n'),(53,6,'<p>Green construction in traditional Kerala style architecture with wooden walls and carvings under slopping tiled roof.100 years old cottages is reconstructed with architectural excellence. The resort is constructed without disturbing the nature. Traditionally designed villas give way to endless views of the enchanting forests which stretch for miles.it is a place where your body can relaxes and tension, worries fade away.</p>\n'),(54,4,'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:muli,sans-serif\">Imagine traditionally constructed houses with laterite stones and clay tiled roofs, in between the lush green rainforest and paddy fields. The family cottages here&nbsp;have two separate rooms and a veranda to enjoy the surroundings, but no Wi-Fi or a TV.</span></span></p>\n'),(55,10,'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:rgb(246, 246, 246); color:rgb(32, 33, 36); font-family:roboto,sans-serif\">This state of the art beach house which offers a magnificent view of the Arabian Sea is in a quiet corner of Vypin Island. Come enjoy breathtaking view and great sunsets!</span></span></p>\n'),(56,2,'<p>At this tree house, we have gone to great lengths to ensure that you experience a truly indigenous way of living. Every aspect of the treehouse experience&nbsp; is designed to develop a deeper appreciation and respect for the earth and its environment. In essence it&nbsp;embodies a &quot;Journey back to Nature&quot;...</p>\n'),(13,5,'<p>It is in the Cardamom Hills near Thekkady and the Periyar Tiger Reserve, in the Idukki District. It&nbsp;offer you to a beautiful stay which reminds you of home but with the luxuries to make you and your loved ones have a memorable time while enjoying and being one with nature.</p>\n\n<p>The rooms in the resort are equipped with a flat-screen TV. Each room comes with a private bathroom with free toiletries, while some rooms also offer a balcony. All rooms have a wardrobe.</p>\n'),(57,9,'<p>Visitors to the farm can take a bullock cart ride, learn about organic farming, feed the farm animals, enjoy commanding views of the valley flanked by mountains and enjoy a sumptuous meal prepared from the freshest local and organic produce.&nbsp; The farm stay has three well&nbsp; appointed rooms fitted with modern amenities, a separate living room with kitchen attached.</p>\n'),(58,8,'<p>The newly constructed guest house, with good quality teak wood as its skeleton. Large windows, spacious verandas, fire place, attic, partly rocky walls and glass roofs presented it the look of a typical colonial house, very tastefully designed. The green carpeted tea &amp; cardamom plantations, the calm water body running along the border, the majestic view of the green mountain ranges, the wooden benches in the balcony overlooking the green lawn.Kitchen again was well equipped, microwave, toast maker, refrigerator Etc&hellip;.</p>\n'),(12,8,'<p>&nbsp;As a vacation retreat, this property gives the sensation of an exotic far away destination without the hassle of traffic. Luxuriously appointed yet casual and welcoming, this is a boutique accommodation suited to individuals, couples or small families in search of a personalized country retreat.</p>\n\n<p>This plantation House is an ideal place for a plantation stay as well as to see how the spices are grown, harvested and processed. A small, friendly village, where one can see and visit typical Kerala-style homes, is within walking distance.</p>\n'),(15,8,'<p>It is a unique concept of Plantation Resort that can be experienced today. It offers you the most singular experience of being one with nature. Set in exotic settings, it is the perfect holiday home for you to enjoy an array of natural wonders.</p>\n'),(16,6,'<p>This Tea Bungalows with backdrops of spectacular countryside mountain valleys, lochs and wildlife is an ideal base for a perfect holiday.Set in the tranquil location with inspiring landscapes, the buildings are the symbol of the colonial heritage of British Indian Architecture, fully furnished with furniture from the colonial era. Being set amidst the vast expanse of privately owned plantation lands provides exclusivity &amp; privacy. Guided by values, courtesy and attentiveness helps create countless memories.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n'),(17,5,'<p>This private cottage is spread across a vast Cardamom Plantation&nbsp; in Munnar. It features open gardens and features various activities such as ping pong, and a pool table. The rooms of this capture the mystic effervescence of Munnar itself.</p>\n'),(18,2,'<p>This Plantation Treehouse in Baison Valley Munnar&nbsp;create the romance and grandeur of a Hill station. Connected by walking trails through stunningly beautiful tea gardens. Each of the four Tree Houses is unique and handcrafted for honeymooners.</p>\n'),(19,2,'<p>A tree house is errected among five large trees of which one of the trees goes through the middle of the tree house, with a spacious balcony overlooking the KallarNallathani river, the tree house here is exotic of the concept, the structure, and its location.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;This&nbsp;Tree House looks stunning holding close to the real concept of the tree house, except for the entry, where there is a ramp from the rear. Tree houses have a rope ladder. However, we have setup a wooden ramp for guests to walk in and out. The tree house is built with wood and iron to hold it up among the trees, and the roofing is of tin sheets that are most common roofing available in the high ranges of the Western Ghats.</p>\n'),(20,5,'<p>The&nbsp;colonial type building&nbsp;admits 8 boutique rooms with all modern-day amenities and offers exotic views of nature. Drive to the resort itself is a relishing experience, as it is through the village road in Pullivasal Tea Estate &ndash; the most beautiful estate in Munnar, Pothamedu view point, Aattukadu waterfalls and breath taking sunset viewpoints.</p>\n'),(21,8,'<p>It is set amidst trees, herbal hills, valleys swathered in mist with the beauty and tranquility of nature and is just walkable distance from pallivasal- one among the most beautiful Tea plantation of Munnar. The resort crowned with nature.</p>\n\n<p>Fitted with wooden furnishings, the stylish rooms come with a wardrobe and work desk. Shower facilities and free toiletries are in the attached bathroom.</p>\n'),(22,8,'<p>It is a piece of heaven on earth where sunlight filters through a high canopy of leaves; where there&rsquo;s joy in every breath and beauty as far as the eye can see; and peace permeates through the sounds of the wild... In the wooded high ranges of the Western Ghats in Kerala, hidden away in one of the world&rsquo;s eight biodiversity hotspots, is a resort where you cannot just live under tall trees, but experience life in the virgin countryside.</p>\n\n<p>The resort will provide you with a satellite TV and a balcony. Featuring a shower, private bathroom also comes with free toiletries. You can enjoy mountain view and garden view from the room.</p>\n'),(23,5,'<p>Its unconventional style gives you a memorable experience right from the time you enter the resort till the time you leave.&nbsp;<strong>Multi-lingual and multi skilled team</strong>&nbsp;will provide you with top notch service laced with warmth and comfort. there chef will dish out some mouth watering delicacies and teach you to cook too. there guest assistants will interact with you every day, to ensure your comfort. Activities and entertainments in-house will ensure that there is enough to keep the little ones and the grown ups busy.</p>\n'),(24,5,'<p>As the mist falls in Munnar and engulfs the carpet of Tea Plantations,waterfalls and mountains it muffles all other sounds and Peace and Tranquility descends upon this lush green landscape surrounding this Rock Cottage.</p>\n\n<p>It is located in the enchanting environs of Letchmi tea Estate in Munnar blessed with waterfalls, mountains and sprawling tea gardens.&nbsp; Facing this endless expanse of greenery is the perennial waterfall just opposite to the resort formed from mist which descends on the mountains.</p>\n'),(26,6,'<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif\">The bungalow has two luxury bed rooms to accommodate guests. Each room is completely different in its decor and has its distinctive character. Every room is decked with antique furniture &ndash; the grand beds come with inlay woodwork, teak wood dressing tables, dining tables, wardrobes and the fireplaces with their teak wood mantles. The common sit-out tea tables and couches on the verandah keeps to the simplistic cane and teakwood. Paintings, murals and handicrafts play with the contrast and colour of the 150 year-old stone walls and timber floors of the bungalow. Well! With all this you also get a vast lawn in your frontyard, where you can try your hands against your partner and the gusty Chokarmudy winds.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif\">The unique terrain and altitude ranging between 6000 and 7500 feet gives a great opportunity to low altitude treks through lush green tea bushes. The treks usually lead to viewpoints offering breathtaking views of Mt. Chokarmudy range, the rolling valleys, various waterfalls and forests. You can get a first hand experience of tea tasting of the finest Lockhart tea from the estate&rsquo;s best tea tasters and can take a guided tea factory tour to witness the making of the best quality Lockhart tea. You can also enjoy a riverside picnic or ask the Manager to arrange a cultural evening with local musicians and villagers.</span></span></span></p>\n');
