INSERT INTO `tbl_pkg_category_about` VALUES (1,1,'<h1 style=\"text-align:center\">Lorem Ipsum</h1>\n\n<h4 style=\"text-align:center\">&quot;Neque porro quisquam est qui dolorem ipsum quia dolor sit amet, consectetur, adipisci velit...&quot;</h4>\n\n<h5 style=\"text-align:center\">&quot;There is no one who loves pain itself, who seeks after it and wants to have it, simply because it is pain...&quot;</h5>\n\n<hr />\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<div>\n<div style=\"text-align:justify\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.</li>\n	<li>Ut id metus eget purus congue faucibus.</li>\n	<li>Curabitur commodo erat eget risus accumsan pulvinar.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Morbi malesuada quam ut felis ultrices, a porta neque viverra.</li>\n	<li>Vestibulum facilisis mi ac purus porta, at fermentum elit semper.</li>\n	<li>Aenean ac sapien tempor, consectetur eros eget, volutpat libero.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Cras at orci sed justo finibus blandit eu ac nibh.</li>\n	<li>Integer sit amet urna facilisis, pulvinar risus quis, convallis magna.</li>\n	<li>Pellentesque at urna tincidunt, auctor arcu quis, volutpat felis.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n'),(2,3,'<p>testhfgh gfhgfh gfhgf hfghgfh&nbsp;</p>\n'),(3,3,'<p>test</p>\n'),(5,4,'<p>Every destination is a unique experience. To live in the actuality of that destination, we should pay a visit. Chose from our wide range of hand-curated destinations which re as unique as you are.</p>\n'),(8,2,'<p>Kerala is truly the home of the God, the all-encompassing verdant scenario might have enticed the lord to such extent that he decided to make the place his abode.</p>\n\n<p>The major&nbsp;hill stations including&nbsp;Munnar , Vagamon and Thekkady&nbsp;located in the Idukki district of the southwestern Indian state of Kerala are&nbsp;situated at around 1,600 metres&nbsp;above mean sea level,in the Western Ghats mountain range. Those hillstations are&nbsp;an ideal location for adventure seekers, who would like to explore its mystical mountain ranges and the wildlife to its fullest.</p>\n\n<p>The adventure enthusiasts could try hike&nbsp;the mountains,camp in the forest and thus experience the craggy mountains and wildlife of Gods Own Country.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n'),(9,3,'<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:verdana,geneva,sans-serif; font-size:14.4px\">Chokramudi stands as a unique piece of Elevated Mountain at an altitude of almost 7200 feet.Unlike the other hill ranges in Idukki it pose&nbsp;separately and is not attached to any other hills or ranges of hills in Munnar.The base camp of Chokramudi peak is a wonderful experience for those who love to explore the heights.The mysterious calmness and breathtaking views from the camp itself is a unique&nbsp;experience.Grabbing a portion of BBQ and gather around a bonfire with music adds to the unconditional experience of being on the standalone peak under the glazing stars.The off road drive to the campsite and speculative&nbsp;trek to the top of Chokramudi render&nbsp;the lust&nbsp;of adventure junkies who loves to experience the rare.</span></p>\n'),(13,1,'<p>Experience the magical waters of Kerala in all its glory. Do everything that can be done in the still waters. The tour takes you through some of the iconic waters of Kerala. Ho would think of kayaking inside a bird sanctuary. The tour makes you experience the bamboo rafting through the manmade lake in Thekkady through the forest. You get a chance to explore the great backwaters of Alleppey on a shikhara boat. You can also opt for an optional houseboat stay. On reaching Kochi, get a chance to get on a cruise ride if time permits.</p>\n'),(12,1,'<p>The offbeat Kerala tour, as its name suggests takes you through some of the unexplored destinations of the state. This tour is perfect for those who wish to discover the new and travel to relatively less touristic places.</p>\n\n<p>This tour combines some extremely beautiful destinations like Athirappilly waterfalls, Thumboormuzhi, Cherai beach, Malayttoor, Paniyeliporu, pooyamkutti, etc. this is a multi-character tour since it combines hills, beaches, forests and some exceptional landscapes.</p>\n\n<p>A special kerala tour which takes you only through the unexplored turfs and terrains in the central kerala. Most of the destinations of this tour being really famous locally, but is yet to catch the attention of the incoming public. Discover some absolute scenic beauty and go for some extraordinary fun in this specially crafted off beat tour.</p>\n'),(14,1,'<p>Each camp has its own character and so is the experience. If you are mad about camping, to experience the great outdoors, this tour is for you. This tour gives the traveler a vivid camping experience where we will be camping in different camps.</p>\n\n<p>This is an exclusive camping tour crafted for those who have a great enthusiasm for camping. This tour clubs in some of the most wonderful and sought after camping experiences. It lets you experience camping from different perspectives maki9ng you camp in places with distinct ambience. You will be experiencing camps of Mankulam- a jungle camping, Suryanelli- an uphill camp andVagamon- a sidehill farm camp.</p>\n'),(15,1,'<p>This is a one of its kind tour which let you experience 5 nights of stay in 5 facilities of distinct character. You will be staying in a bungalow, a tent camp, a houseboat, a plantation cottage and a homestay in these 5 nights in Kerala. This can be an enormous experience being experiencing all types of living in a single tour to the God&rsquo;s own Country.</p>\n'),(16,4,'<p>Kerala, the god&rsquo;s own country is definitely in the bucket list of most travelers. This experience tour let you explore this green paradise in every possible way. In this special Kerala tour, there is everything clubbed in that any traveler would expect on a Kerala tour. From the eye catchy hills of Munnar, to the spice plantations of Thekkady, to mighty backwaters of Alleppey, this tour has it all.</p>\n'),(17,3,'<p><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:raleway,sans-serif; font-size:16px\">Kanthaloor is situated at above 5500 ft above sea level and has a very pleasant climate.With its sprawling tea estates, rolling hills, waterfalls, picture - postcard hamlets, Kanthalloor has the makings of an idyllic holiday destination.It provides the cool climate for the natural farming of fruits like Apple, Orange, Strawberry, Blackberry, Plums, Gooseberry, Egg fruits, peach, Sugarcane, passion fruits. etc.</span></span></p>\n'),(18,3,'<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:calibri,sans-serif; font-size:19px\">Referred to as the heaven on earth, exotic and pristine, Marayoor is a unique place where beauty meets adventure. The enchanting tourist destination of Marayoor offers diversity in every aspect of the land and culture...... hamlets, rocky hills, rivers, brooks, cave temples, paddy and sugar cane fields, waterfalls, sandal wood and bamboo forests...&hellip;This rain shadow region, blessed with abundant natural beauty and wildlife, attracts tourists from all over the world.</span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-family:calibri,sans-serif; font-size:19px\">Marayoor is not only an ideal tourist destination but it also claims to be a part of the Stone Age Civilization that is as old as 10,000 B.C. The land and its unique dolmens, caves, rock edicts and engravings declare its rich heritage. The scenic Marayoor is also noted for its natural growth of sandal wood trees and sprawling wild life. Marayoor travellers often find themselves in the middle of history, nature and adventure. Marayoor is still a pristine, celestial and unexplored tourist spot when compared to Munnar which happens to be one of the most sought after hill stations in India</span></p>\n'),(19,3,'<p><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:raleway,sans-serif; font-size:16px\">Kanthaloor is situated at above 5500 ft above sea level and has a very pleasant climate.With its sprawling tea estates, rolling hills, waterfalls, picture - postcard hamlets, Kanthalloor has the makings of an idyllic holiday destination.It provides the cool climate for the natural farming of fruits like Apple, Orange, Strawberry, Blackberry, Plums, Gooseberry, Egg fruits, peach, Sugarcane, passion fruits. etc.</span></p>\n'),(20,3,'<ul>\n	<li>02 Bedroom rock cottage stay at Marayoor</li>\n	<li>Minimum 6 people required</li>\n	<li>Night jeep safari</li>\n	<li>BBQ available at extra cost</li>\n	<li>Forest experience</li>\n</ul>\n'),(10,4,'<p><a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyderabad,_India\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background: none;\" title=\"\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Hyderabad</span></a><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">&nbsp;is the&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_state_and_union_territory_capitals_in_India\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"List of state and union territory capitals in India\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">capital</span></a><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">&nbsp;and largest city of the&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_India\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"South India\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">South Indian</span></a><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">&nbsp;state of&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telangana\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Telangana\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Telangana</span></a><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">. It was ruled by the&nbsp;</span></span><a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Qutub_Shahis\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Qutub Shahis\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Qutub Shahis</span></a><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">,&nbsp;</span></span><a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mughals\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Mughals\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Mughals</span></a><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">&nbsp;and the&nbsp;</span></span><a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nizams\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Nizams\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Nizams</span></a><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">&nbsp;which shaped its&nbsp;</span></span><a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_Hyderabad,_India\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"History of Hyderabad, India\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">history</span></a><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">. The city is noted for its monuments which includes the masterpiece of&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charminar\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Charminar\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Charminar</span></a><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">&nbsp;and the fort of&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golkonda\" style=\"text-decoration-line: none; color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\" title=\"Golkonda\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Golconda</span></a><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-family:sans-serif; font-size:14px\">. There are a multitude of masjids, temples, churches and bazaars in the city.</span></span></p>\n'),(22,4,'<p>This tour of the heaven on earth is a total holiday which lets you to explore the most visited places in Kashmir. This place is a real heaven when it comes to its beauty. There are numerous options for us to explore in Kashmir around the year but the favourite is the spring which starts from February to early may.</p>\n\n<p>The most famous places here like Dal lake, Gulmarg, Pahalgametc are covered in this awesome experiential&nbsp;tour.</p>\n'),(23,4,'<p>Darjeeling can be termed as the gateway to the northest. This region is very famous for the tea estates and the te produced here re of high quality and export oriented. This region is blessed with nature&rsquo;s untouched beauty and is&nbsp; real abode of nature. Sikkim with its unmatched chrm is another attraction of this tour. The fast developing state is also famous among the traveling community for its richness of tourism resources. Places like Gangtok, kalimpongetc adds glory to its name.</p>\n'),(24,2,'<p>This is an absolutely spine chilling tour which will take you through some of the extreme terrains of Rajasthan. Rajasthan, a western state in India is home to a very rich tradition and its own unique culture. This tour lets you explore the unheard side of Rajasthan. Sansariis&nbsp; very scenic village in Rajasthan where we can experience the real essence of discovering the unexplored terrains on foot.</p>\n'),(25,2,'<p>The Kashmir Great Lakes trek is a trekking journey of 8 days and the trekking is best done during the period of July till September when the meadow track remains filled with blooming flowers and verdant greenery. The Kashmir Great Lakes trek is ideal for the nature lovers who wishes to bask in the charming beauty of lush landscapes, verdant meadows, fresh water lakes and myriad collection of wild flora at the backdrop of stunning peaks.</p>\n'),(26,2,'<p>This one of its kind adventure is a special expedition to Spiti valley can be the most exciting tour in the Himalayan terrain. This is a 9 day long Jeep expedition I which you will be exploring the whole region in an adventurous Jeep safari. The tour let you discover Spiti valley in a whole and gives us&nbsp; chnce to sneak through every single perspective.</p>\n'),(7,4,'<p>A resort town located on the banks of beas river, Manali is one of the most visited destinations in India.It is situated at a distance of around 550km from the national&nbsp;capital , the destination is an year round heaven for travelers.</p>\n\n<p>One can reach Manali from Delhi by road and by air through Kullu airport. Both Volvo bus , common commute bus and private taxi are available from Delhi.Kullu and Shimla can be combined enroute.</p>\n\n<p>In Manali you can visit Hidimba Devi temple, Manu Temple , Mall road, Solang Valley and can also go for a trip to Rohtang pass. Adventure seekers can go for activities like Paragliding , Cable car , Skeiing , White water rafting etc :</p>\n'),(27,3,'<p>mm</p>\n'),(6,1,'<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"color:rgb(84, 84, 84); font-family:arial,sans-serif; font-size:small\">The&nbsp;</span><strong>Hornbill Festival</strong><span style=\"color:rgb(84, 84, 84); font-family:arial,sans-serif; font-size:small\">&nbsp;is a celebration held every year from 1 - 10 December, in Nagaland, Northeast India. It is also called the &#39;Festival of Festivals&#39;.</span></li>\n	<li>To encourage inter-tribal interaction and to promote cultural heritage of Nagaland, the Government of Nagaland organizes the Hornbill Festival every year in the first week of December. The first festival was held in 2000.</li>\n	<li>\n	<p>The festival is named after the Indian hornbill&nbsp;the large and colourful forest bird which is displayed in the folklore of most of the state&#39;s tribes.</p>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Accessibility:</strong> The Hornbill Festival venue -&nbsp;<strong>Naga Heritage Complex</strong>&nbsp;is at&nbsp;<strong>Kisama&nbsp;village situated 12 km</strong> away from Kohima on NH-39 (Imphal highway). The venue for the <strong>Rock concert is&nbsp;either at IG Stadium Kohima</strong>, 20 km from Kisama or Dimapur. Nagaland is well connected by Road, Air, and Train. Nearest Airport and Railway station are at&nbsp;<strong>Dimapur</strong>&nbsp;which is at a distance of 70 km from the state capital Kohima. Regular shared vehicles are available from&nbsp;Dimapur Railway Station/airport.&nbsp;Guwahati to Dimapur&nbsp;is connected by various trains and&nbsp;<strong>Shatabdi-12067</strong>&nbsp;is the best option. By road, it is 340 Km and around 8 hour&rsquo;s journey from Guwahati. Daily overnight buses from&nbsp;<strong>Guwahati &nbsp;ISBT</strong>&nbsp;are available. Private vehicles on hire are available from Guwahati and Jorhat.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Campsite</strong>:&nbsp;Pre-pitched Dome and Alpine shaped tents 02-sharing, 03-sharing and 04-sharing with Sleeping Bags/Blankets-Mats will be provided by us. Other available facilities are 24 hours access to water, common Lobby and Charging Plug Points, Angami Naga Kitchen, Snacks, eco-friendly toilet-bathrooms and&nbsp;<strong>Hot water&nbsp;on request</strong>. The campsite is&nbsp;<strong>100 Meters</strong>&nbsp;away from the main stage and just behind the festival police outpost. The campsite is on the terraces overlooking the Kohima town.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n'),(21,4,'<p><span style=\"font-family:verdana,sans-serif\">Himachal Pradesh tourism draws millions of visitors who love to spend their holidays in relaxed atmosphere and relaxing sylvan environment. With our customize package of&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;5 Nights and 6 Days Shimla - Manali tour, explore the destinations of&nbsp;Shimla and Manali which is one of the significant areas in Himachal. Explore the spectacular natural charm of this Northern State of India.</p>\n'),(28,3,'<p>It&nbsp;is located, to perfectly blend into the forest, so you can enjoy your own private jungle and the spectacular view of the River Periyar. Along its banks, birds flock in their thousands and the cool ambience is the ultimate prize for the birder. Known as the Birder&#39;s Paradise, the&nbsp;Camp and the adjoining Dr Salim Ali Bird Sanctuary, is home to over 300 species of birds, including all the endemics. Mottled Wood Owl, Brown Wood Owl, Spot-bellied Eagle Owl, Malayan Night Heron, Sri Lanka Frogmouth, Rusty-tailed Flycatcher, Grey-headed Bulbul, Nilgiri Wood Pigeon are some of the rarer species found here</p>\n');
