INSERT INTO `tbl_pkg_category_itenary` VALUES (1,1,1,'dfg dfgdfg','<p>df gdfg</p>\n'),(2,1,1,'dfg','<p>dfgdfgdfg</p>\n'),(4,3,3,'Day1','<p>test</p>\n'),(5,3,3,'Day2','<p>test</p>\n'),(6,4,2,'mn   n n ','<p>,m mn n&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n'),(7,5,4,'Manali experience','<p>dvsdvfbrbrsv</p>\n'),(8,2,3,'dfgdfgdf','<p>gdfgdfgdfgdfg</p>\n'),(30,8,2,'Day 1','<p>Pick up from Cochinand transfer to Munnar.Check Inn at Campsite or British tea Bungalows , follows a soft trek , bornfire , dinner and Overnight stay&nbsp;</p>\n'),(31,8,2,'Day2','<p>After breakfast full day trekk with packed lunch.</p>\n'),(32,8,2,'Day 3','<p>After BF Transfer to tekkady and check Inn to a spice plantation guest house&nbsp;</p>\n'),(51,9,3,'Day 1','<p>Arrive at Baison Valley and&nbsp;report at the pick up point.From there you will be transferred to the campsite in an off road jeep through &nbsp;spice&nbsp;plantations.Reaching campsite ,&nbsp;settledown and take a walk through the plantations near camp premises and enjoy the breath taking view of Chokramudi peak.Enjoy your BBQ and delecious dinner around a bonfire on the aura of soft musical&nbsp;night and plunge&nbsp;into the dreams,&nbsp;beneath&nbsp;the glazing sky.</p>\n'),(52,9,3,'Day 2 ','<p>After breakfast , backpack and proceed to conqure the heights of Chokramudi - The standalone peak in Munnar ,and after that move on to a private waterfalls and take a bath and return home with the fulfillment of acheiving the rare.</p>\n'),(159,15,1,'Day 1','<p>You will be greeted and picked up from Airport by our representative and will proceed for the transfer to Munnar. Experience the western Ghats enroute and stop for photostop at Vallara and Cheeyapara waterfalls. You will be taken directly to the ancient British mansion bungalow. The stay is situated in midst of tea plantations. Explore the vicinity and experience the way those royals lived. Overnight stay.</p>\n'),(160,15,1,'Day 2','<p>Wake up to a beautiful day to an inspiring sunrise. Go for a plantation walk and trek to the nearby tea factory. Later checkout and proceed for camp. Check-in to camp. Light trek. Enjoy the evening by the bonfire tasting the yummy barbecue. Overnight stay at the camp.</p>\n'),(161,15,1,'Day 3','<p>Explore the beautiful Sunrise of Kolukumalai in an energetic sunrise trek. Return back to have breakfast and later checkout. Now we will be transferred to Thekkady. Enjoy with elephants at elephant Camp. Checkin to the plantation cottage/homestay. Live in midst of the spicy aroma of those spice plantations of Thekkady. Stay overnight there.</p>\n'),(162,15,1,'Day 4','<p>After breakfast, start the transfer to Alleppey. On arrival, we will be cheched in to the ever famous floating homes &ndash; the houseboat. Enjoy the delicious Kerala meals being served there. Experience the life over waters this night and stay overnight there.</p>\n'),(163,15,1,'Day 5','<p>Have a delicious breakfast and checkout from the houseboat.Transfer to Kochi. Take a stroll through the historical streets of Fort Kochi and visit the Jew Synagogue there which is a reminiscence of the past. Check-in to a homestay and feel the warmth of hospitality of the hosts there.</p>\n'),(164,15,1,'Day 6','<p>After breakfast, checkout and proceed your journey back home for the drop at airport.</p>\n'),(172,17,3,'Day 1','<ul>\n	<li>Check into cottage</li>\n	<li>BBQ &amp; Campfire facility</li>\n</ul>\n'),(173,17,3,'Day 2','<ul>\n	<li>Off road drive</li>\n	<li>Erichipapara falls</li>\n	<li>Apple farm</li>\n</ul>\n'),(174,18,3,'Day 1','<ul>\n	<li>Check Into farm cottage</li>\n	<li>Campfire and BBQ facility available</li>\n	<li>Self Cooking Kitchen Available&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Overnight stay</li>\n</ul>\n'),(175,18,3,'Day 2','<ul>\n	<li>Proceed to Off road drive</li>\n	<li>Pampar River bath</li>\n	<li>Marayoor sandal woods visit</li>\n</ul>\n'),(176,19,3,'Day 1','<ul>\n	<li>Check into cottage</li>\n	<li>Overnight Stay</li>\n	<li>Bonfire and BBQ facility available at extra cost</li>\n</ul>\n'),(177,19,3,'Day 2','<ul>\n	<li>Check out from cottage</li>\n	<li>Proceed to off road drive</li>\n	<li>Visit Muniyara</li>\n	<li>Visit Sandalwoods etc</li>\n</ul>\n'),(178,20,3,'Day 1','<ul>\n	<li>Check into cottage</li>\n	<li>Followed by Dinner&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Night Jeep safari</li>\n	<li>Overnight stay</li>\n</ul>\n'),(179,20,3,'Day 2','<ul>\n	<li>Have Breakfast</li>\n	<li>Check out</li>\n</ul>\n'),(220,10,4,'Day1','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Arrival &amp; Hyderabad Sightseeing</p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">Pickup from Railway Station / Bus Station and proceed to Hotel. After freshup, proceed below to Hyderabad Sightseeing Places including: &nbsp;</span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Birla Mandir<span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> - </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">2000 tonnes of </span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">white marble from Rajasthan mixed with 10 years of </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">dedicated work of sculptures &ndash; created this captivating Temple, standing on a 280 feet high hill. &nbsp;</span>Birla Planetarium<span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> - Developed with </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">technological assistance from Japa</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">n with cosmic presentation of international standards. Most attractive feature is the Sky Show.</span></p>\n\n<p>Birla Science Museum<span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> - showcases many sections, each dedicated to a specific field - </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">Interactive Science Section, NRSA</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">, Dinosaurium, etc.</span></p>\n\n<p>Snow World<span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> - India&rsquo;s first and World&rsquo;s best snow theme park helps to experience snow fall and polar climate as if it is a polar region, then proceed to:</span></p>\n\n<p>Lumbini Park<span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> - Lush greenery, entertaining rides, calm environment all at one place. </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">Must watch - Laser Show and Musical fountain show in the evenings. Boating at Hussain Sagar lake not to be missed.</span></p>\n\n<p>NTR Gardens <span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">- Ride on a toy train, </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">Japanese garden, Desert Garden</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">, Roaring Cascade, Giant Wheel, boating, car cafes, machan Restaurant- just a few attractions of NTR Gardens.</span></p>\n\n<p>Overnight stay at Hyderabad Hotel</p>\n'),(221,10,4,'Day 2','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Full Day Ramoji Film City</p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">After Breakfast, proceed to visit primary tourist place of Hyderabad,</span><a href=\"http://www.hyderabadtourism.travel/ramoji-film-city-hyderabad\" style=\"color: rgb(17, 85, 204); text-decoration-line: none;\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> </span></a><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">Ramoji Film City. Full day would be nearly sufficient at Ramoji Film City.</span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Ramoji Film City -<span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">One of the largest and glamorous film studios in the world, Ramoji Film City has also secured a place in the Guinness Book of World Records. Captivating architecture of the studios accompanied with a range of modern settings makes it a favourite place of film-makers; while a wide array of entertainment choices makes it a popular choice of tourists.</span></p>\n\n<p><em>Overnight stay at Hyderabad Hotel.</em></p>\n'),(222,10,4,'Day 3','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">Morning after Breakfast proceed to:</span></p>\n\n<p><br />\nSalar Jung Museum<span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> - </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">3rd largest museum in Indi</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">a with 43000 art objects (Indian Art, Far Eastern Art, European Art, Middle Eastern Art, etc.), 9000 manuscripts and 47000 printed books, spread in 38 galleries. Not to be missed- Veiled marble statue of Rebecca, 19th C British Musical Clock, etc. </span></p>\n\n<p>Chowmahalla Palace<span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> - </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">Built in the 18th century during the rule of fifth Nizam, Afzal-ud-Daula, Asaf Jah V</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">, said to resemble Shah Palace of Tehran in Iran in its architectural beauty.</span></p>\n\n<p>Charminar <span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">- </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">Built in 1591 by Sultan Mohammed Quli Qutb Shah</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> in the honour of his wife Bhagmati. Also known as known as &lsquo;Arc de Triomphe of the East&rsquo;</span></p>\n\n<p>Mecca Masjid<span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> &ndash; constructed by S</span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">ultan Muhammad Quli Qutub Shah in 1614</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">; one of the largest mosques in the world. To see- Belgian crystal chandeliers, intricately designed arches, tombs to asif shah dynasty.</span></p>\n\n<p><br />\n<em>Overnight stay at Hyderabad Hotel.</em></p>\n'),(223,10,4,'Day 4','<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\">Check-out, Optional Hyderabad Sightseeing &amp; Departure</p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">Morning after Breakfast, check-out from the hotel. Depending on your departure time, if time permits, we can recommend few more tourism places.</span></p>\n\n<p><br />\nJagannath Temple - <span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">Hyderabad&rsquo;s replica of the original Puri Jagannath Temple</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> of Orissa. Built with 600 ton of sandstone brought from Orissa and by about 60 artisans.</span></p>\n\n<p>Golconda Fort<span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> </span>-<span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> First built by Kakatiya dynasty later developed by Qutub Shahi Kings</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">. Attractions- sound and light show in night; Water supply system, &#39;Rahban&#39; cannon, Ramdas&rsquo; prison. </span><span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">(You can also view our team created video on Golconda Fort here). It would take at least half day here..</span></p>\n\n<p>Qutub Shahi Tombs - <span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">One of the oldest monuments of Hyderabad; tombs of seven Qutub Shahi rulers</span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\"> presenting a beautiful blend of Persian and Indian architectural styles.</span></p>\n\n<p><br />\n<span style=\"color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:10pt\">Drop at Hyderabad Airport / Railway Station / Bus Stand for your return journey. </span></p>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n'),(275,11,2,'test1','<p>ARRIVE &ndash; SRINAGAR</p>\n\n<p>In time transfer to airport to connect the flight for Srinagar.Meeting and assistance on arrival and transfer to Hotel. Afternoon 01 Hour Boat Ride on Dal Lake by a gondola Boat called &ldquo;SHIKARA&rdquo; witness the ride on lake, called Venice of India &amp; experience the aquatic life of Srinagar. Also see the scenic extravaganza of the Kashmir and enjoy the profusion of colors in the Paradise on Earth. While returning visit to the local crafts market and see the fine carved hand-made articles from Paper Machie&amp; wood of a walnut. Overnight at the Deluxe Houseboat.</p>\n'),(276,11,2,'test2','<p>SRINAGAR &ndash; SONAMARG &ndash; SRINAGAR (86 KM, 3-4 Hrs Drive one way)</p>\n\n<p>After breakfast leave with full day excursion for Sonamarg. Situated at an altitude of 9000 Ft. Sonamarg &ndash; 84 Kms is also called as &ldquo;The meadow of gold&rdquo; has, as its backdrop, snowy mountains against a cerulean sky. The Sindh River that meanders through the valley abounds with trout and mahaseer. Ponies can be hired for the trip up to Thajiwas glacier, which is a major local attraction during the summer. Return for Dinner &amp; overnight stay HB / Hotel.</p>\n'),(277,11,2,'day3','<p>SRINAGAR &ndash; PAHALGAM (98 KM, 3-4 Hrs Drive one way)</p>\n\n<p>Transfers from Srinagar to Pahalgam called as &ldquo;Valley of Shepherds. On arrival check in at Hotel. In Pahalgam, Enjoy the nature &amp; walk around the banks of River Lidder. Pahalgam is famous for some trekking routes also &amp; is the base camp for Amarnath Pilgrimage. Overnight stay at Hotel.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n'),(278,11,2,'day4','<p>PAHALGAM &ndash; SRINAGAR + LOCAL SIGHTSEEING</p>\n\n<p>Transfers from Pahalgam to Srinagar.Enroute visiting the Awantipura Ruins of 9th Century &amp;Mattan Temple Complex. In Afternoon, visit Mogul Gardens &ldquo;Nishat&rdquo; (The Garden of Pleasure) and &ldquo;Shalimar&rdquo; (Abode of All). Drive along the Lake side on Boulevard On return visit a local Handicrafts Emporium for hand-knotted specialty silken carpets, shawls, jewellery ornaments. Also visit Shankaracharya Temple. Overnight at the Hotel</p>\n'),(279,11,2,'day5','<p>SRINAGAR &ndash; GULMARG &ndash; SRINAGAR (58 KM, 1-2 Hrs Drive one way)</p>\n\n<p>Full Day return excursion to Gulmarg, called as &ldquo;Meadow of Flowers&rdquo; Gulmarg is 53 Kms from Srinagar at an altitude of 8700-ft. Gulmarg also referred as Meadow of Flowers is a famous Ski Resort &amp; the world&rsquo;s highest 18 hole Golf Course. The place was prominent during the British time. Enjoy the scenic view of Kongdori on a Cable Car Ride &ndash; OPTIONAL (Gondola) Return to Srinagar for a Dinner &amp; Overnight at the Hotel.</p>\n'),(280,11,2,'day6','<p><span style=\"font-family:century gothic,sans-serif; font-size:16px\">In time transfer to airport to connect the flight for onwards destination.</span></p>\n'),(287,23,4,'Day 01: NJP Rly Station / IXB Airport – Darjeeling (98 kms / 3 hrs)','<p>Meet &amp; Greet on arrival at NJP Railway Station / IXB Airport &amp; transfer to Darjeeling (6,710 ft.).On arrival check-in to hotel &amp; rest of the day at leisure.Overnight stay at Darjeeling.</p>\n'),(288,23,4,'Day 02: Darjeeling Sightseeing','<p>Early Morning (at 04:00 am) drive to Tiger hill to watch the spectacular sunrise over Mt. Khangchendzongha (28,208 ft. Worlds 3rd highest peak), on your way back visit Ghoom Monastery and Batasia Loop. After breakfast visit Himalayan Mountaineering Institute, P.N. Zoological Park (Thursday closed), Tenzing Rock, Tibetan Refugee self-help Centre (Sunday closed), Tea Garden (outer view) and Japanese Temple (4 hrs from 9.00 to 13.00 hrs). Evening free for shopping &amp; leisure.Overnight stay at Darjeeling.</p>\n'),(289,23,4,' Day 3: Darjeeling – Kalimpong (57 kms / 2 hrs) Sightseeing','<p>After Breakfast transfer to Kalimpong (4,100 ft.). On arrival check-in to your hotel. Afternoon enjoy half day tour of Kalimpong Visit MangalDham, Deolo Hill, Dr. Graham&rsquo;s Home, Golf Garden, Durpin Dara Hills &amp; Flowers Nurseries. Overnight stay at Kalimpong.</p>\n'),(290,23,4,'Day 4: Kalimpong – Gangtok (77 kms / 3 hrs) Local Sightseeing','<p>After breakfast transfer to Gangtok (5,480 ft.). On arrival check-in to your hotel. Afternoon proceed for a half day city tour visiting Banzakhri Falls, Cottage Industry and Handicraft Centre, Flower show, Dro-dulChorten&amp; Institute of Tibetology (maximum 3-4 hours). Overnight stay at Gangtok.</p>\n'),(291,23,4,'Day 5: Excursion to Tsomgo Lake & Baba Mandir','<p>After breakfast start for an excursion to Tsomgo Lake (12,400 ft.) &amp; Baba Mandir (13,200 ft.) which is 55 kms from Gangtok city. Overnight stay at Gangtok. (In case of Land slide or any other reason Tsomgo Lake is closed we will provided alternate sightseeing.)</p>\n'),(292,23,4,'Day 6: Gangtok – NJP Rly Station / IXB Airport (125 kms / 4 hrs)','<p>After breakfast check out from hotel in time and take the departure transfer to NJP Railway Station / IXB Airport for your onward journey.</p>\n'),(299,21,4,'Day 1 : DELHI – SHIMLA ( 370 KM / 8 HRS )','<p><span style=\"color:#222222; font-family:century gothic,sans-serif; font-size:11.0pt\">Pick up from Delhi airport/railway station &amp; drive to Shimla travel by surface, Enjoy the Scenic Himalayas from the window of your cab when you enter Himachal Pradesh . On the ways, stopover at Pinjore Garden and&nbsp;rope way&nbsp;at Timber Trail Resort if time permits. Cab will pass through Panipat, Kurukshetra, Ambala, Kalka, Parwanoo, Barog and Solan on the way to Shimla. Check in and overnight stay in Hotel.</span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#222222; font-family:century gothic,sans-serif; font-size:11.0pt\">Overnight stay at Hotel and dinner in Shimla.</span></p>\n'),(300,21,4,'Day 2 : SHIMLA - KUFRI - LOCAL SIGHTSEEING - SHIMLA (25KMS)','<p>After breakfast ,proceed towards Green Valley , Kufri , Chini Bunglow , Jakhoo Peak &nbsp;site seen and after wards visit Local site seen including The Mall Road, Ridge, Kali Bari Devi Temple, Sankat&nbsp; Mochan Temple, Christ church , Overnight stay at the hotel in Shimla.</p>\n'),(301,21,4,'Day 3 : SHIMLA –KULLU- MANALI (270 KM/8HRS )','<p>After breakfast , check out from the hotel and proceed to Manali (8 hrs.) On the way take a Look at Sunder Nagar Lake , Pandoh Dam,Kullu Valley , Rafting Point , Vaishno Devi Temple. Arrival in&nbsp; Manali , Check into Hotel , overnight stay at the Manali.</p>\n'),(302,21,4,'Day 4 : ROHTANG PASS ','<p>Early Morning move to Rohtang Pass around 06:00 Am , The Zig Zag Journey amidst lush green meadows will enthrall us until we get the snow clad surface of Rohtang Mountain (Snow Line ). After noon you will get back to Solang valley where we can enjoy the enormous activities like Paragliding , Zorbing etc , back Manali ,overnight stay at Manali.</p>\n\n<p>(Up to Snow Line in case Rohtang is closed due to snow fall)&hellip;&nbsp;</p>\n'),(303,21,4,'Day 5 : MANALI  HALF  DAY  CITY  TOUR ','<p>After breakfast , proceed to&nbsp; half day city tour visiting Hadimba Devi Temple ,Van Vihar ,Club House, Vashisht Temple,&nbsp; Tibetan- Monastery, After then ,Mall road ,overnight stay at Manali</p>\n'),(304,21,4,'Day 6 : MANALI-DELHI (575 kms / 12 hrs )','<p>After breakfast, check out from the hotel and drive to Delhi. Arrive Delhi and dropping at Railway Station/Airport</p>\n'),(325,22,4,'Day 1 ARRIVE – SRINAGAR','<p><span style=\"font-family:century gothic,sans-serif; font-size:16px\">In time transfer to airport to connect the flight for Srinagar.Meeting and assistance on arrival and transfer to Hotel. Afternoon 01 Hour Boat Ride on Dal Lake by a gondola Boat called &ldquo;SHIKARA&rdquo; witness the ride on lake, called Venice of India &amp; experience the aquatic life of Srinagar. Also see the scenic extravaganza of the Kashmir and enjoy the profusion of colors in the Paradise on Earth. While returning visit to the local crafts market and see the fine carved hand-made articles from Paper Machie&amp; wood of a walnut. Overnight at the Deluxe Houseboat.</span></p>\n'),(326,22,4,'Day 2  SRINAGAR – SONAMARG – SRINAGAR (86 KM, 3-4 Hrs Drive one way)','<p>After breakfast leave with full day excursion for Sonamarg. Situated at an altitude of 9000 Ft. Sonamarg &ndash; 84 Kms is also called as &ldquo;The meadow of gold&rdquo; has, as its backdrop, snowy mountains against a cerulean sky. The Sindh River that meanders through the valley abounds with trout and mahaseer. Ponies can be hired for the trip up to Thajiwas glacier, which is a major local attraction during the summer. Return for Dinner &amp; overnight stay HB / Hotel.</p>\n'),(327,22,4,'Day 3  SRINAGAR – PAHALGAM (98 KM, 3-4 Hrs Drive one way)','<p>Transfers from Srinagar to Pahalgam called as &ldquo;Valley of Shepherds. On arrival check in at Hotel. In Pahalgam, Enjoy the nature &amp; walk around the banks of River Lidder. Pahalgam is famous for some trekking routes also &amp; is the base camp for Amarnath Pilgrimage. Overnight stay at Hotel.</p>\n'),(328,22,4,' Day 4  PAHALGAM – SRINAGAR + LOCAL SIGHTSEEING','<p>Transfers from Pahalgam to Srinagar.Enroute visiting the Awantipura Ruins of 9th Century &amp;Mattan Temple Complex. In Afternoon, visit Mogul Gardens &ldquo;Nishat&rdquo; (The Garden of Pleasure) and &ldquo;Shalimar&rdquo; (Abode of All). Drive along the Lake side on Boulevard On return visit a local Handicrafts Emporium for hand-knotted specialty silken carpets, shawls, jewellery ornaments. Also visit Shankaracharya Temple. Overnight at the Hotel</p>\n'),(329,22,4,'Day 5  SRINAGAR – GULMARG – SRINAGAR (58 KM, 1-2 Hrs Drive one way)','<p>Full Day return excursion to Gulmarg, called as &ldquo;Meadow of Flowers&rdquo; Gulmarg is 53 Kms from Srinagar at an altitude of 8700-ft. Gulmarg also referred as Meadow of Flowers is a famous Ski Resort &amp; the world&rsquo;s highest 18 hole Golf Course. The place was prominent during the British time. Enjoy the scenic view of Kongdori on a Cable Car Ride &ndash; OPTIONAL (Gondola) Return to Srinagar for a Dinner &amp; Overnight at the Hotel.</p>\n'),(330,22,4,'Day 6','<p>In time transfer to airport to connect the flight for onwards destination with sweet memmories.&nbsp;</p>\n'),(331,24,2,'DAY 1 : UDAIPUR / JODHPUR TO SANSARI','<p>Today we will&nbsp; arrive at Udaipur / jodhpur airport and the after arrival drive to sansari rustic adventure camp. On arrival at camp check in to the camp.After leisure at time.Evening free for village jeep safari.Dinner&nbsp; and enjoy with culture program.Overnight stay at camp.</p>\n'),(332,24,2,'DAY 2 : SANSARI trek [ Mata magri – Vasor Village – Mayli Mata Valley – Japaliya Dam – Rustic adventure camp ]','<p>Today after morning breakfast we start our trek from camp pass through&nbsp; an incredible&nbsp; villages and hills, ponds, rivers. Packed lunch at maylimata valley, after lunch take some rest then proceed for trek .Evening back to camp.Dinner and overnight stay at camp</p>\n'),(333,24,2,'DAY 3 : SANSARI TO SUMER [ UmanaBera – UparlaGuda – KotSolankiyan – Khimaj Mata Valley – Sumer ] ','<p>Today after morning breakfast&nbsp; check out from camp and we start our trek from camp pass through&nbsp; an aravali hills, Packed lunch at khimajmata, after lunch take some rest then proceed for trek . on arrival at sumer check in to the old&nbsp; jungle loudge ( Bagho-ka-bagh). Dinner and overnight stay at sumer.&nbsp;</p>\n'),(334,24,2,'Day 4 : SUMER TO KUMBHALGARH [ Kumbhalgarh Century ]','<p>Today after morning breakfast&nbsp; check out from bagho-ka-bagh and&nbsp; trek to kumbhalgarh on trek spotting some&nbsp; interesting species birds and trees,&nbsp; completing trek after visit kumbhalgarh fort. Overnight at kumbhalgarh.</p>\n'),(335,24,2,'Day 5 : KUMBHALGARH TO RANAKPUR [ Tour End ]','<p>Today after breakfast check out from hotel and drive to Thandi very. Thandi very is starting point of a trek to Ranakpurmuchalamahavirjaintemple .reach at last ending point the drive to Udaipur enroute visit world famous jain temple. This temple is most importance to the Jain community across&nbsp; the country. After visit drive for Udaipur airport for your onward journey.</p>\n'),(345,25,2,'DAY 1 : Srinagar – Sonmarg (Alt 7800 ft)','<p>Drive from Srinagar and arrive in Sonmarg which is 3 hours&rsquo; drive. Sonmarg is a beautiful meadow land with greenery and nature bliss. Night halt in camps.</p>\n'),(346,25,2,' DAY 2 : Sonamarg to Nichnai via Shekdur (Alt 7,800 ft to 11,500 ft)','<p>Trekking starts this day and approx 6-8 hours trek to Nichnai via Shekdur. The trail takes you through meadows, dense forests with Maple, Pine and Bhoj trees. The trek from Shitkadi to Shekdur is goes through thick forests of pine trees and will take approx 2 and half hours. The trek follow the Nichnai Stream as we trek from Shekdur to Nichnai. Overnight at tents at our camps.</p>\n'),(347,25,2,'DAY 3 : Nichnai to Vishansar lake via Nachnai Pass (Alt: 11,500 ft to 12,000 ft via 13100 ft)','<p>A 12 kms trek that takes approx 8 hours We can visit the Vishansar Lake which is just 15 minutes&rsquo; walk from the campsite The first lake of the trek and one of the most beautiful ones. Vishansar is visited by hoards of sheep and their shepherds are known for interesting stories.</p>\n'),(348,25,2,'DAY 4 : Rest Day.','<p>Rest day or say acclimatization day for rest of the trekking. Visit Kishansar Lake, which is at approx 1 and half kms from our camp site.</p>\n'),(349,25,2,'DAY 5 : Vishansarlake to Gadsar via Gadsar Pass (Alt 12,000 ft)','<p>Start the trek little earlier in the morning. The trail passes from Vishansar to Gadsar, via Gadsar pass the highest point of the trek. We can see the Kishansar Lake on the way. After the Gadsar Lake, we will reach the campsite in 2 hours. Check our ID&rsquo;s in an army check point. Night halt in tents.</p>\n'),(350,25,2,'DAY 6 : Gadsar to Satsar (Alt 12,000 ft)','<p>On this day trek we see two small lakes which are often mistaken as Satsar Lakes. We will visit the Satsar twin lakes, in the afternoon. These twin lakes are between the middle of the mountain.</p>\n'),(351,25,2,'DAY 7 : Satsar to Gangabal twin lakes via Zaj Pass (Alt 13000 ft)','<p>Walk on rocky paths for approx an hour and ascend till Jazz Pass. At the pass, you can enjoy views of the 4 lakes, Mt. Harmukh and its glacier. We visit the Gangbal Lake, which is one of the largest lakes in the trek.</p>\n'),(352,25,2,'DAY 8 : Gangabal to Naranag Drive to Srinagar','<p>Descent trek to Naranag which will pass through pine tree forest. Drive back to Srinagar and after reaching Srinagar night halt at our houseboat.</p>\n'),(353,25,2,'DAY 9 : Departure day.','<p>Our representative shall assist you to the airport. If there are few hours to spare (depending upon the time of the flight), we can organize a sightseeing trip in Srinagar</p>\n'),(354,26,2,'Day 1 : Chandigarh-Sangla','<p>We will pick you from Chandigarh Airport / Railway Station and start drive to Sangla. Check in to the Hotel. dinner and overnight stay in Sangla.</p>\n'),(355,26,2,'Day 2 : Sangla-Chitkul -Kalpa','<p>Travel by surface from Sangla to KalpaEnroute visiting Chitkul village. The Picturesque town of Sangla located on the Banks of the famous Baspa River provides an Ideal location for Adventure Activities as well. Kalpa village is located in backdrop of Kenner Kailash mountain range. Dinner and overnight stay.</p>\n'),(356,26,2,'Day 3 : Kalpa- Nako- Tabo','<p>Travel by surface from Kalpa to Nako which is located by the banks of lake. Visit the monastery and walk around Village. Later continue drive Enroute viewing confluence of Satluj&amp;Spiti Rivers at Khab.. On arrival in Tabo, check in at hotel. Evening visit Tabo Monastery which was founded in 996 AD by the great teacher Richensang-po, Tabo is renowned for its breathtaking murals and stucco images &ndash; and is often called &ldquo;The Ajanta of the Himalayas. Overnight at Hotel/ Home Stay.</p>\n'),(357,26,2,'Day 4 : Tabo- Dhankar - Kaza','<p>Travel by surface from Tabo to KazaEnroute visiting, Dhankar Monastery &amp;Lalung. Reach Kaza in the evening On arrival check in at guest house Overnight at Hotel / Home stay.</p>\n'),(358,26,2,'Day 5 : Local Sight Seeing Tour in Kaza','<p>Morning visit the famous Ki monastery, 12 kms from Kaza. This century &ndash; old Gompa is a labyrinth of rooms and corridors &ndash; and at one time also acted as a fort. Also visit the small gompa at Kibber, Hikkim ,Komik And Langza 9 kms further ahead. Dinner Over Night stay at Hotel/Home Stay</p>\n'),(359,26,2,'Day 6 : Kaza-Losar -Kunzum Pas - Chandertal Lake','<p>After breakfast drive to Chandertal Lake. You will cross Kunzum La Pass and reach Chandertal in the evening Dinner and over night stay in Kaza hotel</p>\n'),(360,26,2,'Day 7 : Chandertal -Rohtang- Manali','<p>After breakfast Check out and Drive to Manali..On Arrival&nbsp;Check In . Dinner and Overnight stay in hotel by own.</p>\n'),(361,26,2,'Day 8 : Manali – Chandigarh','<p>Today morning after breakfast Check out from the hotel and drive to Chandigarh. Our cab will drop you at desired point .</p>\n'),(362,26,2,'Day 9 : Chandigarh','<p>Today morning after breakfast Check out from hotel and make your arrangement to move further.</p>\n'),(363,7,4,'Day 1 - Delhi to Manali  Evening Volvo','<p>Once you have reached Delhi by your personal mode of transportation, head to Firoz Shah Kotla Stadium, Gate No. 3. At&nbsp;5 PM, you will depart for Manali in a Volvo. The distance between Delhi and Manali is 580 kms, making your travel time from Delhi to Manali around 11-12 hours. Manali has been an inspiration for every kind of traveller. A soulful town, it is known for offering something special to everyone. Be it a person looking for solitude or adventure enthusiasts yearning for another thrilling activity, Manali never disappoints. An excellent place for vacation, your overnight journey to Manali is bound to be tranquil and breezy. The landscapes you will encounter on your journey are sure to stay with you long after you have finished your trip to the mountains.</p>\n'),(364,7,4,'Day 2 - Manali reach and local sightseeing','<p>Manali reach early morning. Take some rest and then proceed for local sightseeing. After that come back to hotel, dinner and overnight stay at Hotel.</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Hadimba Devi Temple:-</strong>&nbsp;It chief central of interest in Manali , dedicated to the goddess Hadimba , the Wife of Bheema of Mahabharata Fame, This is wooden temple, In the dense forest of magnificent deodar, is about 2.5 Kms from the Mall. It is a pleasant stroll to the temple which was built in 1553 A.D.</li>\n	<li><strong>Vashisht:-</strong>&nbsp;Hot Sulphur Water springs &ndash; which is widely believed as an effective skin diseases healer and posses various medical properties . Nearby it , is the pyramidal stone temple dedicated to vashisht Muni &amp; lord Rama temple.</li>\n	<li><strong>Tibetan-</strong>Monastery:- This Gadhan Thekchoking Gompa dominates the Tibetan area builtin 1969. The main attraction of the monastery is the handicrafts of Tibetan artistry and the carpets that are woven and sold in the monastery</li>\n	<li><strong>Club House :-</strong>&nbsp;Club house is famous for a amusement activities like skating, Disco Theque, auditorium etc. Later in the evening free to explore the Shopping Malls (Mall Road &amp; IBEX Market) of Manali. Dinner &amp; Overnight at Manali Hotel.</li>\n</ul>\n'),(365,7,4,'Day 3 - Manali-Snow Point ','<p>Early morning after breakfast start for full day sight seeing to snow point / Rohtang Pass) and on the way back from Rohtang Pass / Snow point visit Solang Valley. Solang Valley, is located in between the Beas Kund and Solang village. This serene valley presents stunning views of snow clad mountain peaks and glaciers. Also famed as Snow Point, this valley is popular for skiing, parachuting, hiking, paragliding and zorbing.</p>\n\n<p>(Note: Rohtang Pass visit will depend upon government permission and Weather conditions on Direct payment Basis.)</p>\n'),(366,7,4,'Day 4 :Kullu Full Day trip','<p>After morning breakfast proceed to Visit :&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Kullu Shawl factory</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Kullu water rafting Point</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Vaishno Devi Temple</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Manikaran Spring Water</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Manikaran Gurudwara</p>\n\n<p style=\"margin-left:36.0pt\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Manikaran Shiv Temple</p>\n\n<p><strong>En route Visit :</strong></p>\n\n<p>Kullu Manali :- at the northern end of the Kullu Valley in Himachal Pradesh, is a hill station situated at a height of 2050 m (6398 ft) in the Himalayas. Situated on the Beas river (Vyaas in Hindi) and near its source, it is a popular tourist spot for Indians in summer and a magical, snow-covered place in winter. A staging point for a number of treks (Beas Kund, Chandrakhani Pass) and sports such as white-water rafting, Manali is also on the road to Ladakh via the valley of Lahaul and Spiti and rohtang pass which is main attraction near manali. Dinner &amp; overnight stay at hotel at Manali.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n'),(367,7,4,'Day 5 : Manali to Delhi','<p>Today After morning breakfast Check out from the hotel at&nbsp;10:00 am.&nbsp;Enjoy the Mall Road. Evening start journey from Manali to Delhi.</p>\n'),(368,7,4,'Day 6 - Reach Delhi','<p>By noon reachs Delhi and tour Ends With Sweet Memories Remain</p>\n'),(374,6,1,'Day 1 : Airport-Kohima','<p>On arrival at Guwahati/Dimapur, directly transfer to Kisama Heritgae Village (Hornbill venue) and check in to your tents. Evening, visit the festival venue. Evening bonfire and overnight at the camp.&nbsp;</p>\n'),(375,6,1,'Day2 : Kohima (Hornbil venue):','<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">&nbsp;After breakfast, visit the festival ground which is just around 150 meters from the festival ground. Witnes the naga heritage and cultural shows. Evening you will have the option to explore Kigwema and Jakhama village or go for rock concert at IG stadium or explore the Kohima city.</span></p>\n'),(376,6,1,'Day 3 : Kohima (Khonoma tour):','<p>&nbsp;After breakfast, half day experience the festival venue and second half depart for Khonoma village tour. Our local guide will join you at the village. Late afternoon, return to Kohima and you will have the options to explore Kohima city with night bazaar or you can go to IG stadium for rock shows. Evening bonfire, get briefing for the next day Dzukou trek and overnight at the camp.</p>\n'),(377,6,1,'Day 4 : Kohima (Dzukou Trek)','<p>Early morning at around 6 AM, depart for Viswema village (around 30+ km) to the last motorable point with your packed breakfast and lunch. Start your trek to Dzokou around 03 hours. Explore the valley for around 03 hours and have lunch at the base camp. At around 1Pm, start your return trek to the pickup point. Evening, visit the festival venue or rock show. Bonfire and overnight at the camp.</p>\n'),(378,6,1,'Day 5 : Kohima-Airoport/Railways station drop','<p>&nbsp;After breakfast, check out from the campsite and get transferred to the airport/railway station of Dimapur or Guwahati city. Tour ends.&nbsp;</p>\n'),(379,12,1,'Day 1 : Kochi','<p>Upon arrival, pick up and transfer to hotel in Kochi. Local site seeing if time permits. Spent the rest day there</p>\n'),(380,12,1,'Day 2 : Athirappilly Waterfalls','<p>Once done with the breakfast, we will embark on the full day tour for one of the most visited waterfall of south India, the Athirappilly waterfalls. Enroutespend some time at the Thumboormuzhy check dam and click some photos in its picturesque backdrop. Return back to hotel and overnight stay there.</p>\n'),(381,12,1,'Day 3 : Cherai Beach','<p>&nbsp;After breakfast, we will proceed to explore the Fortkochi in all its detail. Spent some time walking through the Jew street, visit the Synagogue, test your cameras at the fort kochi beach and stare at the Dutch palace. Then we will go for an evening visit of Cherai beach, one of the most prominent beach in Kochi. Witness the inspiring sunset at the Kuzhuppilly beach, an&nbsp;offbeat destination situated nearby. Return to hotel after the well spent day and stay overnight at hotel.</p>\n'),(382,12,1,'Day 4 : Thattekkad Bird Sanctuary Visit & Kayaking','<p>Wake up to a wonderful day and embark onn the full day trip to Thattekad bird sanctuary. See some unique species of birds in there and feel the ambience of real nature. Visit enrouteMalayattoor and Paniyeliporu, two great unexplored places situated nearby. Stay at Kothamangalam.</p>\n'),(383,12,1,'Day 5 : Pooyamkutti Forest','<p>Once breakfast is over, we will embark on a tour of Pooyamkutti forest. Explore the raw Western Ghats and experience the beauty of virgin nature there. Later return to airport for the drop and travel back home with best of the memories.</p>\n'),(384,13,1,'Day 1 : Nature Camp at Thattekkad','<p>Once arrived, transfer to Thattekad. We will be let to experience the magnificence of nature in a camp inside the Thattekad bird sanctuary. Take a walk around the facility and explore the life on the banks. Overnight stay there.</p>\n'),(385,13,1,'Day 2 : Kayaking at Thattekkad','<p>Kayaking and trek at Thattekkad backwaters and&nbsp;camp. O/N stay.</p>\n'),(386,13,1,'Day 3 : Thekkady','<p>Transfer to Thekkady. Half day sightseeing.</p>\n'),(387,13,1,'Day 4 : Bamboo rafting and Cruise boat ride','<p>Full day river rafting in Thekkady.</p>\n'),(388,13,1,'Day 5 : Alleppyy','<p>After breakfast, transfer to Alleppy. On reaching, half day shikhara ride. Stay</p>\n'),(389,13,1,'Day 6 : Kochi','<p>After breakfast, transfer to Kochi. Optional lake cruise. Drop.</p>\n'),(390,14,1,'Day 1','<p>Pickup from airport-transfer to Mankulam. On reaching Mankulam, check in to the tent. You will be greeted with a welcome drink. Enjoy your uphill beside a bonfire gazing the stars.</p>\n'),(391,14,1,'Day 2','<p>Take an early morning trek and come back to have breakfast. Checkout from the camp and proceed for a sightseeing tour of Munnar. Once it&rsquo;s done we will proceed to the next campsite which is on the highest point of Munnar. Reach there after a short trek and get recharged on the welcome drink there. The evening will be spent beside a bonfire tasting the delicious barbeque.</p>\n'),(392,14,1,'Day 3','<p>The day will start with a sunrise trek to the famous trek Kolukumalai. Once done go for a natural bath in the nearby waterfall along with a plantation walk. Later get your hands on the activities like kayaking, ziplining etc. come back and rest by the bonfire and later have dinner.</p>\n'),(393,14,1,'Day 4','<p>So, this morning, explore the unexplored ends of the plantations there and have the tasty breakfasts. Once it&rsquo;s done its time for us to move on to the next camping site in Vagamon. After a 3 to 4 hour drive, we will be reaching our campsite. Here, we will be greeted with some organically prepared drinks. The will be left for exploring the farm and can do some cultivation there. Spend spent the eve realizing the nature. Dinner there.</p>\n'),(394,14,1,'Day 5','<p>Take a stroll through the plantations on the misty morning and come back to have the organic breakfast. Once done with breakfast, spend some time in gardening and cultivation. Later checkout and proceed for an enroute sightseeing tour of Vagamon. Reach airport after a 3 hour journey and return back with the memories of a cherishing experience.</p>\n'),(400,16,4,'Day 1 : Arrival & Transfer to Munnar','<p>On arrival at airport/ railway station, you will be greeted and transferred towards Munnar. Travel through the mystic forests of Western Ghats over a 4 hour long drive and enroute visit Vallara and Cheeyapara waterfalls. On reaching, check-in at hotel/resort. Overnight stay there.</p>\n'),(401,16,4,'Day 2 : Munnar Sightseeing','<p>Wake up to one of the most exciting day and proceed for breakfast. This day will be spent on sightseeing. We will explore the popular tourist destinations nearby. You can have some optional activities to experience in the day. Later return to hotel. Overnight stay there.</p>\n'),(402,16,4,'Day 3 : Thekkady','<p>After breakfast, we will start our journey towards the land of spices &ndash;Thekkady. Feel the real aroma of different spices all through the route. Go for a sightseeing tour of Periyar Wildlife Sanctuary and experience the boating in the manmade lake through the forests(optional). Later return to the hotel and stay overnight.</p>\n'),(403,16,4,'Day 4 : Alappey ','<p>Once the breakfast is done, we will move on to one of the highlight experience of our tour, the houseboat in Alleppey. On reaching Alleppey after a 30 minutes long drive through changing terrains, we will check- in to the awaited houseboat on the renowned backwaters of Alleppey. Will start our ride on it while having a delicious Kerala lunch. Spend the day enjoying the distinct experience floating over the backwaters.</p>\n'),(404,16,4,'Day 5 : Return to Kochi','<p>Wake up to a great morning, checkout after a yummy breakfast and proceed towards Kochi. Explore a little according to the time left and later fly back home with brainful of memories and heartful of love of this God&rsquo;s own country.</p>\n'),(406,28,3,'Day Outing Package','<ul>\n	<li>Check into the camp by 10 Am</li>\n	<li>Welcome Drink on arrival</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;Lunch (with 2 Non Veg dishes)- Buffet</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;Evening Tea &amp; Snacks</li>\n	<li>Guided 01 hour Kayaking at Periyar River</li>\n	<li>01 hour cycling</li>\n	<li>&nbsp;Soft trekking at Dr. Salim Ali Birding trail</li>\n	<li>Usage of Indoor and outdoor activities viz. Cricket, Volley Ball, Badminton, Tug-of-War, Caroms, Chess, Frisbee, Darts, Turnball junior etc.</li>\n</ul>\n');
